## 2. Key Concepts

### 2.1 What is Generative AI

* Type of AI focused on **creating new content** (text, code, images, etc.) rather than only analyzing existing data. [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
* Core distinction:
  * Traditional AI → classification, prediction
  * Generative AI → **content generation**

***

### 2.2 Core Technologies Behind Generative AI

* Built on **Large Language Models (LLMs)** such as Claude. [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
* Enabled by:
  * **Transformer architecture** (key algorithmic breakthrough) [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
  * **Large-scale training datasets** [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
  * **High-performance computing infrastructure** [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)

***

### 2.3 How Generative AI Works

* Training process:
  * **Pre-training** → model learns general language patterns from massive datasets [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
  * **Fine-tuning** → adjusts behavior for specific tasks or alignment [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)

* Key concepts:
  * **Context window** → amount of input the model can consider at once [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)
  * **Emergent capabilities** → unexpected abilities that appear at scale [\[Generative...ndamentals\]](https://anthropic.skilljar.com/ai-fluency-framework-foundations/291879)

***

### 2.4 Capabilities of Generative AI

* Generate human-like:
  * Text (documentation, chat, summaries)
  * Code
  * Creative content
* Can assist in:
  * Automation of knowledge work
  * Decision support (when guided properly)

***

